Maori itch
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:usually aplied to irritating skin eruptions, or the bites of fleas or body lice; hakihaki (ake-ake)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca 1935 Havelock Don't play too much with Maoris. You'll get Maori itch. It burrows underneath your skin and no amount of scratching will get rid of it.
